#* {{quote-web|en|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2018/04/planets-are-built-from-pebbles/558854/|title=Earth May Have Been Formed by a Bunch of Tiny Space Pebbles|date=2018-04-26|author=Alexandra Witze|work=The Atlantic|passage=Chris Ormel, an astronomer at the University of Amsterdam, and his colleagues recently calculated that protoplanets began to form at the snow line around the star, then grew quickly by '''accreting''' pebbles.}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[adhere]]; to grow or to be added to gradually.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make [[adhere]]; to add; to make larger or more, as by growing.
#* '''1871''', {{w|John Earle (professor)|John Earle}}, ''The Philology of the English Tongue''
#*:the reader has not only mastered this distinction , but that he has so thoroughly '''accreted''' it and assimilated it to his habits of mind

